    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Ultimate Equipment pg. 20</em>, <em>Adventurer's Armory pg. 5</em>, <em>Ultimate Combat pg. 144</em></p><h3><span title=\"PFS Legal\">[PFS]</span> Statistics</h3><p><strong>Cost</strong> 30 gp <strong>Weight</strong> 3 lbs.</p><p><strong>Damage</strong> 1d6 (small), 1d8 (medium); <strong>Critical</strong> x3; <strong>Range</strong> -; <strong>Type</strong> P; <strong>Special</strong> performance</p><p><strong>Category</strong> One-Handed; <strong>Proficiency</strong> Exotic</p><p><strong>Weapon Groups</strong> Blades, Heavy</p><h3>Description</h3><p>The shotel is a downward-curving sword designed to reach over or around an opponent's shield. You gain a +1 bonus on attack rolls with a shotel against opponents using bucklers, light shields, or heavy shields. The curve of a shotel's blade varies from sword to sword, and some models are double-edged, while others are single-edged, with the back edge able to be braced against a shield for additional power. Shotels are particularly useful for hooking mounted combatants and ripping them from their steeds.</p>"
